# .kilocodeignore — keeps heavyweight reference material out of the runtime agent's context.
#
# Kilo Code (and Roo Code via .rooignore conventions) auto-includes workspace files in
# context. On 128K-class models (DeepSeek, GLM) one auto-included sample lorebook can eat
# a third of the window. Nothing below is needed while RUNNING the pipeline.
#
# NOTE: if you are doing MAINTENANCE on the pipeline itself (editing agent_roles/,
# templates/, workflows/) from inside Kilo, temporarily comment out the CLAUDE.md and
# CHANGELOG.md lines — they are the maintenance context.

# Sample world outputs (>1 MB total) — reference for humans, noise for a pipeline run
Samples/

# Maintenance / meta documentation — not needed at runtime
CLAUDE.md
CHANGELOG.md
wiki/
tutorial.md
LICENSE
